Backend Setup
The backend should handle authentication, invoice fetching, and triggering the Zapier automation.

1. Set up a Node.js/Express Backend
Initialize a new Node.js project
download all the required module

# mkdir backend
# cd backend
# npm init -y
# npm install express axios
# npm install google-auth-library

2. Implement Google OAuth Verification (replace the given code)
Create middleware to verify Google ID tokens:

3. Set Up API Endpoints 
Create API endpoints for fetching invoices and triggering automation:

4. add .env file which include-
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=177804601405-hdefp254umn564e3oms14plvu9ltsu6q.apps.googleusercontent.com
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_actual_google_client_secret
ZAPIER_WEBHOOK_URL=https://hooks.zapier.com/hooks/catch/123456/abcdef
SESSION_SECRET=your_actual_session_secret


5. Connect both frontend and backend

